==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[congregatus]]'', past participle of ''[[congregare]]'' to congregate; ''[[on-]] + [[gregare]]'' to collect into a flock, from grex flock, herd.  See [[gregarious]].

===Adjective===
'''congregate'''
# [[collected|Collected]]; [[compact]]; [[close]]. [R.]

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|congregat|e}}

# {{tag|transitive}}: To collect into an assembly or assemblage; to assemble; to bring into one place, or into a united body; to gather together; to mass; to compact.
